6→    \"url\": \"https://developers.openai.com/codex/changelog/\",\n    37→    \"date\": \"2026-03-02\",\n    38→    \"community_feedback\": []\n    39→  },\n    40→  {\n    41→    \"productName\": \"Windsurf\",\n    42→    \"title\": \"GPT-5.4 and New Model Picker\",\n    43→    \"description\": \"Windsurf added GPT-5.4 support with limited-time promotional pricing (No Reasoning: 1x credits, Low: 1x, Medium: 2x, High: 3x, Extra High: 8x). Also introduced a new model picker that groups models by family with hovercards for variant toggles.\",\n    44→    \"updateType\": \"feature\",\n    45→    \"url\": \"https://windsurf.com/changelog\",\n    46→    \"date\": \"2026-03-05\",\n    47→    \"community_feedback\": []\n    48→  },\n    49→  {\n    50→    \"productName\": \"Windsurf\",\n    51→    \"title\": \"Cascade and Platform Improvements\",\n    52→    \"description\": \"Enhanced Cascade with POST_CASCADE_RESPONSE_WITH_TRANSCRIPT hook, added Cascade hooks configuration visibility on team settings, improved file search performance, and merged VS Code 1.108 changes. Fixed Windows update initialization path and released Linux ARM64 binaries.\",\n    53→    \"updateType\": \"bugfix\",\n    54→    \"url\": \"https://windsurf.com/changelog\",\n    55→    \"date\": \"2026-02-26\",\n    56→    \"community_feedback\": []\n    57→  },\n    58→  {\n    59→    \"productName\": \"Gemini CLI\",\n    60→    \"title\": \"Agent Skills and Event-Driven Architecture\",\n    61→    \"description\": \"Introduced skill-creator skill, enabled agent skills by default, and added a generalist agent for improved task routing. Implemented new event-driven scheduler for tool execution resulting in more responsive performance.\",\n    62→    \"updateType\": \"feature\",\n    63→    \"url\": \"https://geminicli.com/docs/changelogs/\",\n    64→    \"date\": \"2026-01-27\",\n    65→    \"community_feedback\": []\n    66→  },\n    67→  {\n    68→    \"productName\": \"Gemini CLI\",\n    69→    \"title\": \"New /rewind Command and Linux Clipboard Support\",\n    70→    \"description\": \"Added /rewind command for easier session history navigation and Linux clipboard support for Wayland and X11. Enhanced UI with queued tool confirmations and expandable large text pastes.\",\n    71→    \"updateType\": \"feature\",\n    72→    \"url\": \"https://geminicli.com/docs/changelogs/\",\n    73→    \"date\": \"2026-02-03\",\n    74→    \"community_feedback\": []\n    75→  },\n    76→  {\n    77→    \"productName\": \"Aider\",\n    78→    \"title\": \"Model Support Expansion\",\n    79→    \"description\": \"Added support for Claude 4.5/4.6 models, Gemini 2.5 Flash/Flash-Lite, Gemini 3 preview models, DeepSeek Reasoner, and OpenAI GPT-5.1/5.2/5-pro models across multiple providers. Updated gemini alias and added o1-pro model support.\",\n    80→    \"updateType\": \"feature\",\n    81→    \"url\": \"https://aider.chat/HISTORY.html\",\n    82→    \"date\": \"2026-02-20\",\n    83→    \"community_feedback\": []\n    84→  }\n    85→]\n    86→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"
