        "content": "     1→[\n     2→  {\n     3→    \"title\": \"Perhaps not Boring Technology after all\",\n     4→    \"description\": \"Simon Willison challenges the concern that LLMs for programming will push technology choices toward well-represented tools in training data. He reports that modern coding agents work excellently with brand new or private tools, thanks to long context lengths that can consume documentation and learn patterns from existing codebases. This contradicts the expectation that coding agents would enforce 'Choose Boring Technology' principles.\",\n     5→    \"author\": \"Simon Willison\",\n     6→    \"source\": \"Blog\",\n     7→    \"url\": \"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Mar/9/not-so-boring/\",\n     8→    \"published_date\": \"2026-03-09\",\n     9→    \"topics\": [\"LLM programming\", \"coding agents\", \"technology choices\", \"Boring Technology\", \"context length\", \"AI tool adoption\"],\n    10→    \"type\": \"opinion\"\n    11→  },\n    12→  {\n    13→    \"title\": \"Amjad Masad: 'Stop Learning to Code' stance gains traction\",\n    14→    \"description\": \"Replit CEO Amjad Masad's controversial position that learning to code is becoming less important in the AI era gains attention. NDTV reports Masad stating 'learning to code is pointless' as AI builds apps instead, suggesting people should focus on other skills. This highlights the ongoing debate about AI's impact on traditional software development skills.\",\n    15→    \"author\": \"NDTV / Instagram Reel\",\n    16→    \"source\": \"Social Media\",\n    17→    \"url\": \"https://www.instagram.com/p/DVpCoPQIAmv/\",\n    18→    \"published_date\": \"2026-03-08\",\n    19→    \"topics\": [\"AI coding\", \"learning to code\", \"Replit\", \"Amjad Masad\", \"skill transformation\", \"AI education\"],\n    20→    \"type\": \"opinion\"\n    21→  },\n    22→  {\n    23→    \"title\": \"Building grith — OS-level syscall interception for AI coding agents\",\n    24→    \"description\": \"Hacker News discussion about 'grith', a project providing OS-level syscall interception for AI coding agents. The post addresses problems with various coding agents like Cline, Aider, Codex, and Claude Code, focusing on security and control at the operating system level.\",\n    25→    \"author\": \"Hacker News Community\",\n    26→    \"source\": \"HN\",\n    27→    \"url\": \"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47305991\",\n    28→    \"published_date\": \"2026-03-09\",\n    29→    \"topics\": [\"AI coding agents\", \"syscall interception\", \"OS security\", \"Cline\", \"Aider\", \"Codex\", \"Claude Code\"],\n    30→    \"type\": \"technical\"\n    31→  },\n    32→  {\n    33→    \"title\": \"Ask HN: What Are You Working On? (March 2026)\",\n    34→    \"description\": \"Monthly HN thread featuring an 'AI coding CLI' that routes simple tasks to a local LLM and complex tasks to Claude, showcasing hybrid approaches to AI-assisted development.\",\n    35→    \"author\": \"Hacker News Community\",\n    36→    \"source\": \"HN\",\n    37→    \"url\": \"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47303111\",\n    38→    \"published_date\": \"2026-03-09\",\n    39→    \"topics\": [\"AI coding CLI\", \"local LLM\", \"Claude\", \"hybrid AI systems\", \"developer tools\"],\n    40→    \"type\": \"discussion\"\n    41→  },\n    42→  {\n    43→    \"title\": \"Agent Safehouse – macOS-native sandboxing for local agents\",\n    44→    \"description\": \"Discussion about a new tool for sandboxing AI agents running locally on macOS, addressing security concerns around local AI agent execution.\",\n    45→    \"author\": \"Hacker News Community\",\n    46→    \"source\": \"HN\",\n    47→    \"url\": \"https://agent-safehouse.dev/\",\n    48→    \"published_date\": \"2026-03-08\",\n    49→    \"topics\": [\"AI agents\", \"sandboxing\", \"macOS security\", \"local AI\", \"agent safety\"],\n    50→    \"type\": \"discussion\"\n    51→  },\n    52→  {\n    53→    \"title\": \"We should revisit literate programming in the agent era\",\n    54→    \"description\": \"Article arguing that the rise of AI coding agents makes literate programming more relevant than ever, as better documentation and code explanations help AI agents understand and work with codebases more effectively.\",\n    55→    \"author\": \"Silly Business\",\n    56→    \"source\": \"Blog\",\n    57→    \"url\": \"https://silly.business/blog/we-should-revisit-literate-programming-in-the-agent-era/\",\n    58→    \"published_date\": \"2026-03-08\",\n    59→    \"topics\": [\"literate programming\", \"AI agents\", \"code documentation\", \"developer experience\", \"AI-human collaboration\"],\n    60→    \"type\": \"opinion\"\n    61→  },\n    62→  {\n    63→    \"title\": \"Ask HN: Please restrict new accounts from posting (AI-generated posts concern)\",\n    64→    \"description\": \"Community discussion about the rise of AI-generated posts on Hacker News, particularly from new accounts, and potential solutions to maintain content quality and prevent bot spam.\",\n    65→    \"author\": \"Hacker News Community\",\n    66→    \"source\": \"HN\",\n    67→    \"url\": \"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47300329\",\n    68→    \"published_date\": \"2026-03-08\",\n    69→    \"topics\": [\"AI content\", \"platform moderation\", \"bot detection\", \"community standards\", \"AI-generated content\"],\n    70→    \"type\": \"discussion\"\n    71→  },\n    72→  {\n    73→    \"title\": \"Will the Pentagon's Anthropic controversy scare startups away from defense work?\",\n    74→    \"description\": \"Discussion about the controversy surrounding Anthropic's Pentagon deal and its potential impact on AI startups considering defense contracts.\",\n    75→    \"author\": \"TechCrunch\",\n    76→    \"source\": \"TechMedia\",\n    77→    \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/08/will-the-pentagons-anthropic-controversy-scare-startups-away-from-defense-work/\",\n    78→    \"published_dat