egally challenge the Department of Defense's supply-chain designation, escalating the conflict over AI company defense contracts.\",\n   135→    \"author\": \"TechCrunch\",\n   136→    \"source\": \"TechMedia\",\n   137→    \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/05/anthropic-to-challenge-dods-supply-chain-label-in-court/\",\n   138→    \"published_date\": \"2026-03-05\",\n   139→    \"topics\": [\"Anthropic\", \"Department of Defense\", \"legal action\", \"supply chain\", \"AI regulation\"],\n   140→    \"type\": \"news\"\n   141→  },\n   142→  {\n   143→    \"title\": \"Can coding agents relicense open source through a 'clean room' implementation of code?\",\n   144→    \"description\": \"Simon Willison explores the legal and ethical implications of AI coding agents potentially creating 'clean room' implementations of open source code, raising questions about licensing, derivative works, and the boundaries of AI-generated code.\",\n   145→    \"author\": \"Simon Willison\",\n   146→    \"source\": \"Blog\",\n   147→    \"url\": \"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Mar/5/chardet/\",\n   148→    \"published_date\": \"2026-03-05\",\n   149→    \"topics\": [\"AI coding agents\", \"open source licensing\", \"clean room implementation\", \"legal implications\", \"copyright\"],\n   150→    \"type\": \"technical\"\n   151→  },\n   152→  {\n   153→    \"title\": \"Something is afoot in the land of Qwen\",\n   154→    \"description\": \"Simon Willison discusses recent developments with Qwen (Alibaba's AI model), highlighting significant improvements or changes in the model ecosystem.\",\n   155→    \"author\": \"Simon Willison\",\n   156→    \"source\": \"Blog\",\n   157→    \"url\": \"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Mar/4/qwen/\",\n   158→    \"published_date\": \"2026-03-04\",\n   159→    \"topics\": [\"Qwen\", \"Alibaba AI\", \"LLM models\", \"AI developments\"],\n   160→    \"type\": \"opinion\"\n   161→  }\n   162→]\n   163→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file,