div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"source-badge source-producthunt\">Product Hunt</span>\n                        <span>Released: March 8, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/products/vibe-marketplace-by-greta\" target=\"_blank\">Vibe Marketplace by Greta</a>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">Vibe coding marketplace</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        A marketplace for vibe coding tools that enables developers to sell and distribute what they ship instantly.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"quote\">\"Sell what you ship, instantly\"</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"source-badge source-producthunt\">Product Hunt</span>\n                        <span>Released: March 8, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/products/claude-marketplace\" target=\"_blank\">Claude Marketplace</a>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">AI tool marketplace</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        A marketplace helping companies easily discover and acquire the AI tools they need for developer productivity.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"source-badge source-producthunt\">Product Hunt</span>\n                        <span>Released: March 8, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/products/aura-2\" target=\"_blank\">Aura</a>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">AI code governance</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Semantic version control for AI coding agents on top of Git, providing flawless traceability for AI-generated code by hashing AST instead of lines.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"quote\">\"Block undocumented AI commits\"</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"source-badge source-producthunt\">Product Hunt</span>\n                        <span>Released: March 2, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/products/clean-clode\" target=\"_blank\">Clean Clode</a>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">CLI tool</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        A CLI utility that instantly cleans and formats Claude Code & Codex terminal output for better readability.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"source-badge source-producthunt\">Product Hunt</span>\n                        <span>Released: March 2, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/products/octrafic\" target=\"_blank\">Octrafic</a>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">API testing CLI</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Test your APIs in plain English, straight from the terminal - an AI-powered CLI tool for API testing.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"source-badge source-producthunt\">Product Hunt</span>\n                        <span>Released: March 1, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/products/openfang\" target=\"_blank\">OpenFang</a>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">Agent operating system</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        An open-source agent operating system for running and managing AI agents across different environments.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"quote\">\"Open-Source Agent Operating System\"</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"source-badge source-producthunt\">Product Hunt</span>\n                        <span>Released: March 1, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/products/unblocked-ai-code-review\" target=\"_blank\">Unblocked AI Code Review</a>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">Code review tool</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        AI-powered code review tool that provides high-signal comments based on your team's context and codebase.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"source-badge source-producthunt\">Product Hunt</span>\n                        <span>Released: February 24, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </section>\n\n            <!-- Whitelist Updates Section -->\n            <section class=\"whitelist-updates\">\n                <h2>🔄 Whitelist Updates (8)</h2>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://cursor.com/changelog\" target=\"_blank\">Cursor: Automations Feature Launch</a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type type-feature\">Feature</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Cursor introduced Automations for building always-on agents that run based on user-defined triggers and instructions from sources like Slack, Linear, GitHub, PagerDuty, and webhooks. Agents spin up in cloud sandboxes and have access to memory tools.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"quote\">\"Turns code review and operations into background tasks\"</div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span>March 5, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://docs.devin.ai/release-notes/overview\" target=\"_blank\">Devin: Progressive Web App Support</a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type type-feature\">Feature</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Devin can now be installed as a Progressive Web App (PWA) on desktop and mobile devices through Chrome or Edge browsers, providing easier access without requiring native app installation.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span>March 6, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://developers.openai.com/codex/changelog/\" target=\"_blank\">Codex CLI: GPT-5.4 Model Support</a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type type-release\">Release</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Codex CLI 0.107.0 released with improved approval prompts, app connection sign-in flows, and performance improvements. GPT-5.4 is now available in Windsurf with promotional pricing for different reasoning tiers.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span>March 2, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://windsurf.com/changelog\" target=\"_blank\">Windsurf: GPT-5.4 and New Model Picker</a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type type-feature\">Feature</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Windsurf added GPT-5.4 support with limited-time promotional pricing (No Reasoning: 1x credits, Low: 1x, Medium: 2x, High: 3x, Extra High: 8x). Also introduced a new model picker that groups models by family.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span>March 5, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://windsurf.com/changelog\" target=\"_blank\">Windsurf: Cascade and Platform Improvements</a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type type-bugfix\">Bugfix</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Enhanced Cascade with POST_CASCADE_RESPONSE_WITH_TRANSCRIPT hook, added Cascade hooks configuration visibility on team settings, improved file search performance, and merged VS Code 1.108 changes.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span>February 26, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://geminicli.com/docs/changelogs/\" target=\"_blank\">Gemini CLI: Agent Skills and Event-Driven Architecture</a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type type-feature\">Feature</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Introduced skill-creator skill, enabled agent skills by default, and added a generalist agent for improved task routing. Implemented new event-driven scheduler for tool execution resulting in more responsive performance.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span>January 27, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://geminicli.com/docs/changelogs/\" target=\"_blank\">Gemini CLI: New /rewind Command and Linux Clipboard Support</a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type type-feature\">Feature</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Added /rewind command for easier session history navigation and Linux clipboard support for Wayland and X11. Enhanced UI with queued tool confirmations and expandable large text pastes.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span>February 3, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://aider.chat/HISTORY.html\" target=\"_blank\">Aider: Model Support Expansion</a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type type-feature\">Feature</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Added support for Claude 4.5/4.6 models, Gemini 2.5 Flash/Flash-Lite, Gemini 3 preview models, DeepSeek Reasoner, and OpenAI GPT-5.1/5.2/5-pro models across multiple providers.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span>February 20, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </section>\n\n            <!-- Technical Insights Section -->\n            <section class=\"technical-insights\">\n                <h2>💡 Technical Insights (16)</h2>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Mar/9/not-so-boring/\" target=\"_blank\">Perhaps not Boring Technology after all</a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type type-opinion\">Opinion</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Simon Willison challenges the concern that LLMs for programming will push technology choices toward well-represented tools in training data. Modern coding agents work excellently with brand new or private tools.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"source-badge source-blog\">Simon Willison</span>\n                        <span>Mar 9, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/DVpCoPQIAmv/\" target=\"_blank\">Amjad Masad: 'Stop Learning to Code' stance</a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type type-opinion\">Opinion</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Replit CEO Amjad Masad's controversial position that learning to code is becoming less important in the AI era gains attention.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"source-badge source-twitter\">NDTV / Instagram</span>\n                        <span>Mar 8, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47305991\" target=\"_blank\">Building grith — OS-level syscall interception</a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type type-technical\">Technical</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Hacker News discussion about 'grith', a project providing OS-level syscall interception for AI coding agents, focusing on security and control.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"source-badge source-hn\">HN</span>\n                        <span>Mar 9, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47303111\" target=\"_blank\">Ask HN: What Are You Working On?</a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type type-discussion\">Discussion</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Monthly HN thread featuring an 'AI coding CLI' that routes simple tasks to a local LLM and complex tasks to Claude.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"source-badge source-hn\">HN</span>\n                        <span>Mar 9, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://agent-safehouse.dev/\" target=\"_blank\">Agent Safehouse – macOS-native sandboxing</a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type type-discussion\">Discussion</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Discussion about a new tool for sandboxing AI agents running locally on macOS, addressing security concerns around local AI agent execution.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"source-badge source-hn\">HN</span>\n                        <span>Mar 8, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://silly.business/blog/we-should-revisit-literate-programming-in-the-agent-era/\" target=\"_blank\">Revisit literate programming in the agent era</a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type type-opinion\">Opinion</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Article arguing that the rise of AI coding agents makes literate programming more relevant than ever, as better documentation helps AI agents understand codebases.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"source-badge source-blog\">Silly Business</span>\n                        <span>Mar 8, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47300329\" target=\"_blank\">Ask HN: Restrict new accounts from posting</a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type type-discussion\">Discussion</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Community discussion about the rise of AI-generated posts on Hacker News, particularly from new accounts, and potential solutions to maintain content quality.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"source-badge source-hn\">HN</span>\n                        <span>Mar 8, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/08/will-the-pentagons-anthropic-controversy-scare-startups-away-from-defense-work/\" target=\"_blank\">Pentagon's Anthropic controversy</a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type type-opinion\">Opinion</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Discussion about the controversy surrounding Anthropic's Pentagon deal and its potential impact on AI startups considering defense contracts.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"source-badge source-techcrunch\">TechCrunch</span>\n                        <span>Mar 8, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/07/openai-robotics-lead-caitlin-kalinowski-quits-in-response-to-pentagon-deal/\" target=\"_blank\">OpenAI hardware exec Caitlin Kalinowski quits</a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type type-news\">News</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        OpenAI's robotics hardware lead Caitlin Kalinowski resigns following controversy over Pentagon deals.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"source-badge source-techcrunch\">TechCrunch</span>\n                        <span>Mar 7, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/06/anthropics-claude-found-22-vulnerabilities-in-firefox-over-two-weeks/\" target=\"_blank\">Claude found 22 vulnerabilities in Firefox</a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type type-technical\">Technical</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Report on Anthropic's Claude AI successfully identifying 22 security vulnerabilities in the Firefox browser.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"source-badge source-techcrunch\">TechCrunch</span>\n                        <span>Mar 6, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/06/claudes-consumer-growth-surge-continues-after-pentagon-deal-debacle/\" target=\"_blank\">Claude's consumer growth surge continues</a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type type-news\">News</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Analysis showing Claude's consumer adoption growth continuing despite controversy surrounding Pentagon defense deals.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"source-badge source-techcrunch\">TechCrunch</span>\n                        <span>Mar 6, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/06/city-detect-uses-ai-to-help-cities-stay-safe-and-clean/\" target=\"_blank\">City Detect raises $13M Series A</a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type type-news\">News</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        City Detect, an AI-powered platform for municipal safety and cleanliness monitoring, successfully raises $13M in Series A funding.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"source-badge source-techcrunch\">TechCrunch</span>\n                        <span>Mar 6, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/06/after-europe-whatsapp-will-let-rival-ai-companies-offer-chatbots-in-brazil/\" target=\"_blank\">WhatsApp AI chatbot marketplace expands to Brazil</a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type type-news\">News</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        WhatsApp expands its AI chatbot marketplace to Brazil, following European launch, allowing multiple AI companies to offer chatbots.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"source-badge source-techcrunch\">TechCrunch</span>\n                        <span>Mar 6, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/05/anthropic-to-challenge-dods-supply-chain-label-in-court/\" target=\"_blank\">Anthropic to challenge DOD's supply-chain label</a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type type-news\">News</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Anthropic plans to legally challenge the Department of Defense's supply-chain designation, escalating the conflict over AI defense contracts.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"source-badge source-techcrunch\">TechCrunch</span>\n                        <span>Mar 5, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Mar/5/chardet/\" target=\"_blank\">Can coding agents relicense open source?</a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type type-technical\">Technical</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Simon Willison explores the legal and ethical implications of AI coding agents potentially creating 'clean room' implementations of open source code.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"source-badge source-blog\">Simon Willison</span>\n                        <span>Mar 5, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Mar/4/qwen/\" target=\"_blank\">Something is afoot in the land of Qwen</a>\n                        <span class=\"update-type type-opinion\">Opinion</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Simon Willison discusses recent developments with Qwen (Alibaba's AI model), highlighting significant improvements in the model ecosystem.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                        <span class=\"source-badge source-blog\">Simon Willison</span>\n                        <span>Mar 4, 2026</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </section>\n        </main>\n\n        <footer>\n            <p>📊 Report generated by <strong>Agent Code Daily</strong> - Powered by Claude Agent SDK</p>\n            <p style=\"margin-top: 5px;\">Total: 8 new products • 8 whitelist updates • 16 insights</p>\n            <p style=\"margin-top: 10px; font-size: 10px;\">\n                <a href=\"https://github.com/agentdaily\" target=\"_blank\">GitHub</a> •\n                <a href=\"https://agentdaily.dev\" target=\"_blank\">Website</a>\n            </p>\n        </footer>\n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>",
